We need to produce a "participant key file" for customers that tells them
which GUID relates to each participant. That way when we send them data (or
they take it from the API) they can de-code who is who.

 

Two potential ways of doing it:

 

*	Add anonymous as a flag in the API. Setting anonymous as FALSE would
download the participant table with real names in it.
This would be more secure as it will be easier for us to control the API
using IP whitelists, at least for the next few months. But it means that the
API isn't completely anaonymous
*	Add the ability to download a participant key from the schemeportal
It is possible to edit participants from the scheme portal so we could also
add the ability to download a participant key from there. We had planned to
give scheme owners access to this portal at some point (although we haven't
done it yet) so this would allow them to download their own participant key
without us getting involved. Downside is it will be more difficult to
protect that attack surface?

 

Any preferences or ideas?

 

C


